  "texts": [
    "So, higher weights indicate that the corresponding feature contains more important information for the given taskFig. 5.",
    "Attention techniques are divided into two categories based on calculating attention scores.",
    "(1) Standard vanilla attention and (2) Collaborative attention.",
    "Note Vanilla uses a parameterized content vector, while collaborative attention is related to learning attention weights from two sequences.",
    "In this research, method 1 (formula (3) 47) is used."
